@page "/terms"

<PageTitle>Terms of Use — Star Wars Data</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Terms of use for Star Wars Data Explorer." />
</HeadContent>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Medium" Class="py-8">
    <MudStack Spacing="4">

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" GutterBottom="true">Terms of Use</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.caption" Color="Color.Secondary">Last updated: 29 March 2026</MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">1. What this site is</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            Star Wars Data Explorer (<MudLink Href="https://swdata.ai" Underline="Underline.Always">swdata.ai</MudLink>)
            is a non-commercial, fan-made project built and operated by a single individual (Patrick Magee).
            There is no company, organisation, or legal entity behind it. The site provides interactive
            tools for exploring Star Wars universe data sourced from
            <MudLink Href="https://starwars.fandom.com" Target="_blank" Underline="Underline.Always">Wookieepedia</MudLink>,
            a community wiki licensed under
            <MudLink Href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/" Target="_blank" Underline="Underline.Always">CC-BY-SA 3.0</MudLink>.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">2. No warranties</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            The site is provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; without warranty of any kind. Data accuracy depends on
            the underlying Wookieepedia content. AI-powered features (Ask AI, character timelines,
            relationship graph) may produce inaccurate, incomplete, or fabricated results. Do not rely
            on this site for factual accuracy.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">3. Acceptable use</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            You may use the site for personal, non-commercial purposes. You agree not to:
        </MudText>
        <MudList Dense="true" T="string">
            <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Block">
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">Attempt to access other users' data or accounts.</MudText>
            </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Block">
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">Use automated tools to scrape or overload the site.</MudText>
            </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Block">
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">Attempt to bypass rate limits or authentication mechanisms.</MudText>
            </MudListItem>
            <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Block">
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">Use the AI features for purposes unrelated to Star Wars content.</MudText>
            </MudListItem>
        </MudList>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">4. Accounts and authentication</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            Authentication is provided through Keycloak at
            <MudLink Href="https://auth.magaoidh.pro" Target="_blank" Underline="Underline.Always">auth.magaoidh.pro</MudLink>.
            You may sign in using social login providers (Microsoft, Facebook) or a local account.
            Creating an account is optional &mdash; the site is usable without signing in, with reduced
            functionality (no chat history, lower rate limits).
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">5. Bring Your Own Key (BYOK)</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            Signed-in users may provide their own OpenAI API key for the Ask AI feature. By doing so,
            you acknowledge that your queries are sent directly to OpenAI using your key and are subject
            to <MudLink Href="https://openai.com/policies/terms-of-use" Target="_blank" Underline="Underline.Always">OpenAI's terms of use</MudLink>.
            Your key is encrypted at rest using ASP.NET Core Data Protection and is only decrypted
            at the moment of an API call. The site operator cannot view your key in plaintext.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">6. AI-generated content</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            The Ask AI feature, character timelines, and relationship graph are produced with the
            assistance of OpenAI models. This content may contain errors, hallucinations, or
            inconsistencies with established Star Wars canon or legends. AI-generated content
            should not be cited as authoritative.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">7. Intellectual property</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            Star Wars and all associated names, characters, and content are the property of
            Lucasfilm Ltd. / Disney. Wookieepedia content is used under CC-BY-SA 3.0 and is
            attributed throughout the site. This project does not claim ownership of any
            Star Wars intellectual property. See the <MudLink Href="/about" Underline="Underline.Always">About</MudLink>
            page for a full licensing discussion.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">8. Availability</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            The site is a personal project and may be taken offline, modified, or discontinued
            at any time without notice. AI features depend on OpenAI API availability and quota;
            they may be temporarily unavailable.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">9. Limitation of liability</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            To the fullest extent permitted by law, the site operator is not liable for any
            damages arising from your use of the site, including but not limited to: loss of data,
            inaccurate AI outputs, or charges incurred through your own OpenAI API key (BYOK).
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">10. Changes to these terms</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            These terms may be updated at any time. Continued use of the site after changes
            constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">11. Contact</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            For questions or concerns, contact the site operator via
            <MudLink Href="https://magaoidh.pro" Target="_blank" Underline="Underline.Always">magaoidh.pro</MudLink>
            or through the
            <MudLink Href="https://github.com/pjmagee/starwars-data" Target="_blank" Underline="Underline.Always">GitHub repository</MudLink>.
        </MudText>

    </MudStack>
</MudContainer>
